The course provides an overview of operations related to the management and administration of the organisation, related legislation and regulations and change management.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to get an overview of the actions related to the management and administration of the institution.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student  - recognizes the types of organisations and the legislation and regulations that apply to them;  - knows how to plan and organize management activities based on the organization's instructions and other regulations;  - knows the principles of preparing a risk analysis and can prepare a risk analysis accordingly;  - knows how to plan activities and organize the finding of resources based on the institution's goals;  - is able to monitor the operation of processes in order to intervene if necessary and plan changes in time.
